

P(conformToI | norms) = ( P(norms | conformToI) * P(conformToI) ) / P(norms)

norms = P(empExI AND normCondI)
	  = P(empExI | normCondI) * P(normCondI)
      = ( P(normCondI | empExI) * P(empExI) ) / P(normCondI) * P(normCondI)
      = P(normCondI | empExI) * P(empExI)

normCondI = P(normExI OR sancExI)
          = P(normExI) + P(sancExI) - P(normExI AND sancExI)
          = P(normExI) + P(sancExI) - ( P(normExI | sancExI) * P(sancExI) )



The probability of conforming to a norm is dependent on a populations adherence to a norm:
P(conformToNorm | populationConformToNorm) = ( P(populationConformToNorm | conformToNorm) * P(conformToNorm) ) / P(populationConformToNorm)

The Prior probability P(conformToNorm) is based on contingency / condition rules and personal weights,


A population's conformance to a norm is described as:
P(populationConformToNorm) = P(EmpiricalExpectationToConform) AND P(NormativeOrSanctionableExpectationToConform)

Where NormativeOrSanctionableExpectationToConform is:
P(NormativeOrSanctionableExpectationToConform) = P(NormativeExpectation) OR P(SanctionableExpectationToConform)
                                               = P(NormativeExpectation) + P(SanctionableExpectation) - P(NormativeAndSanctionableExpectation)
                                               = P(NormativeExpectation) + P(SanctionableExpectation) - ( P(NormativeExpectation | SanctionableExpectation) * P(SanctionableExpectation) )

So:
P(populationConformToNorm) = P(EmpiricalExpectationToConform | NormativeOrSanctionableExpecation) * P(NormativeOrSanctionableExpectation)



P(A |(B AND (C OR D))) = P(conform | (emEx AND (normEx OR sancEX)))
